2026-01-29 18:33:07,857 - chains.sql_chain - INFO - Generated SQL: SELECT CustomerID FROM transactions WHERE InvoiceDate = (SELECT MAX(InvoiceDate) FROM transactions); DATABASE SCHEMA: Table: customer_feedback Columns: Table: customer_feedback Description: Feedback provided by customers after purchases. Each feedback is linked to a specific transaction and product, but not all products have received feedback yet. Columns: - CustomerID: Unique identifier for the customer (may be null) - Invoice: Transaction-level data from an online retail store - StockCode: Product code used in inventory system - Rating: Numerical rating given by a customer, on scale of 1 to 5. Null indicates no feedback was provided yet for that product/transaction combination. - Comments: Textual comments left by the customer (can be null) - FeedbackDate: Date and time when the feedback was submitted Derived Metrics: - average_rating: Average rating given to a specific StockCode, excluding NULL values ((SUM(Rating) / COUNT(*))). If no ratings exist for that product/transaction combination (only NULLs), return 'No Ratings'. CONVERSATION CONTEXT: Human: Which products have the highest average customer satisfaction rating and what is their respective StockCode? Please provide feedback only from customers who made a purchase in 2019. Exclude any product that has not received at least one piece of feedback yet, as well as those with NULL ratings or comments. Also include how many times each rated item was reviewed within the year and list them by descending average rating first then alphabetically if there's a tie in their StockCode. Assistant: The SQL query to find this information is complex due to multiple conditions, including filtering feedback from 2019 only for non-NULL entries with ratings of at least one per product/transaction combination and ordering by the highest average rating first then alphabetically if there's a tie in StockCode. Here it is: ```sql SELECT cf.StockCode, COUNT(cf.Rating) AS NumberOfReviews, AVG(cf.Rating) as AverageRating FROM customer_feedback cf JOIN transactions t ON cf.Invoice = t.Invoice AND YEAR(t.InvoiceDate) = 2019 WHERE cf.Rating IS NOT NULL GROUP BY StockCode HAVING COUNT(cf.Rating) > 0 ORDER BY AverageRating DESC, StockCode ASC; ``` If you want to include only those products that have received feedback at least once in the year of interest (2019), we can add a subquery or common table expression with this condition: ```sql WITH FeedbackInYear AS ( SELECT StockCode, Invoice FROM customer_feedback cf JOIN transactions t ON cf.Invoice = t.Invoice AND YEAR(t.InvoiceDate) = 2019 WHERE Rating IS NOT NULL GROUP BY StockCode, Invoice HAVING COUNT(Rating) > 0 ) SELECT f.StockCode, AVG(cf.Rating) as AverageRating, COUNT(f.Invoice) AS NumberOfReviews FROM FeedbackInYear f JOIN customer_feedback cf ON f.StockCode = cf.StockCode AND YEAR(cf.FeedbackDate) = 2019 GROUP BY StockCode HAVING COUNT(f.Invoice) > 0 ORDER BY AverageRating DESC, StockCode ASC; ```
